strings : addCommas

Write a method named addCommas that accepts a string representing a number and returns a new string with 
a comma at every third position, starting from the right. For example, the call of addCommas("12345678") returns "12,345,678".


 public static String addCommas(String str) {
       if(str.length() <= 3) {
            return str;
        }
        List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
        String str2 = "";
        for(int i = 0; i < str.length(); i++) {
            list.add(str.substring(i, i + 1));
        }
        int listSize = list.size();
        for(int i = listSize - 3; i > 0; i-=3) {
          list.add(i, ",");
        }
        for(String string : list) {
            str2 += string;
        }
        return str2;
    }




